Maintainer: Chia-Jung Chang <q2330416@gmail.com>
Description: scONCO is a cancer cell-type annotation framework for
    single-cell RNA-seq data. It combines (i) a 4-level hierarchical
    marker database co-curated by multiple large language models and a
    clinical oncology expert (539 markers x 61 cell types, pan-cancer with
    14 cancer-type modules), (ii) a
    specificity-weighted hierarchical scoring algorithm extending scMRMA
    (Li et al. 2022), and (iii) a statistical confidence layer providing
    hierarchical reject option (de Lichtenberg et al. 2024), split conformal
    prediction with marginal coverage guarantees (Boudaoud et al. 2025),
    AUC-based marker specificity (Pullin and McCarthy 2024), and empirical
    AI / literature support.
